---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — AEROS" description="Building the runtime that embodied agents need — open-core infrastructure for governed deployment.">

  <!-- ═══ Header ═══ -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">About</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">
        Building the infrastructure<br>embodied agents deserve
      </h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Open-core runtime infrastructure for governed embodied deployment.</p>
      <p class="page-desc">
        AEROS builds the runtime layer that turns embodied AI from lab demos into
        governed, production-grade systems. We make deployment <em>safe</em>,
        <em>auditable</em>, and <em>continuous</em>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Mission Statement ═══ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mission-block">
        <div class="mission-quote">
          <p>
            We build governed, evolvable runtime infrastructure for embodied agents.
          </p>
          <p class="mission-sub">
            Not another robot OS. Not another model wrapper.
            A runtime platform that closes the gap between "AI demo" and "AI in production"
            — making it manageable, safe, and auditable for every deployment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Who We Are ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Who We Are</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">From research to runtime</h2>

      <div class="who-block">
        <p>AEROS started as a systems research program — seven papers exploring what it takes to make embodied agents truly deployable. Not just capable. Not just intelligent. Deployable: running continuously, safely, under governance, in the real world.</p>
        <p>We saw that the gap between "AI demo" and "AI in production" for embodied systems wasn't a model problem or a hardware problem. It was a runtime problem. So we built one.</p>
        <p>Today, AEROS is an open-core runtime with an Apache 2.0 core, a growing capability packaging system, and an enterprise governance layer. We're based in Shanghai.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Thesis ═══ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Thesis</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Why embodied agents need runtime infrastructure</h2>

      <div class="thesis-grid">
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">01</div>
          <h3>Models are necessary but not sufficient</h3>
          <p>Foundation models give agents the ability to reason. But reasoning without governance, state management, and lifecycle control is a demo, not a product.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">02</div>
          <h3>Hardware diversity is accelerating</h3>
          <p>Humanoids, quadrupeds, AMRs, drones, collaborative arms — each with different capabilities. Capabilities must be modular, portable, and versionable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">03</div>
          <h3>Production demands governance</h3>
          <p>In warehouses, hospitals, and public spaces, "what happened?" and "who authorized that?" are not optional questions. Runtime governance makes them answerable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Why Now ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Why Now</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">The timing is right</h2>

      <div class="thesis-grid">
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">01</div>
          <h3>Models are ready</h3>
          <p>Foundation models can now reason about physical actions, objects, and environments. The intelligence layer is no longer the bottleneck.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">02</div>
          <h3>Hardware is diversifying</h3>
          <p>Humanoids, quadrupeds, AMRs, collaborative arms — the fleet is getting heterogeneous. A shared runtime layer is no longer optional.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">03</div>
          <h3>Governance is becoming unavoidable</h3>
          <p>As robots move from labs to warehouses, hospitals, and public spaces, policy enforcement, audit, and accountability become regulatory requirements, not nice-to-haves.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Why Us ═══ -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Why Us</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Research depth meets engineering execution</h2>

      <div class="why-us-block">
        <p class="why-us-intro">Most robotics infrastructure is built bottom-up from middleware. AEROS is designed top-down from a governance-first thesis, validated through a 7-paper research program, and implemented as production-grade open-source software.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="thesis-grid">
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">01</div>
          <h3>7 systematic papers</h3>
          <p>Runtime architecture, governance, evolution, contracts, federation, benchmarking. Not isolated publications — a coherent systems program.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">02</div>
          <h3>Open-source MVP</h3>
          <p>Not slides. Running code under Apache 2.0.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="thesis-card">
          <div class="thesis-num">03</div>
          <h3>Single-agent thesis</h3>
          <p>A clear architectural principle that every design decision traces back to.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Milestones ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Timeline</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Milestones</h2>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item done">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2026.04</span>
            <h3>7-paper research program completed</h3>
            <p>Systematic academic foundation covering runtime, governance, evolution, contracts, federation, and benchmarking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item done">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2026.04</span>
            <h3>arXiv preprints published</h3>
            <p>4 papers publicly available for peer review and academic scrutiny.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item done">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2026.04</span>
            <h3>AEROS open source MVP</h3>
            <p>Runtime Core released under Apache 2.0. Project page launched.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2026.H2</span>
            <h3>Runtime Core v1.0</h3>
            <p>Production-ready runtime with full lifecycle management, ECM support, and tracing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2026.H2</span>
            <h3>First pilot deployment</h3>
            <p>Proof-of-concept deployment with a warehouse automation partner.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-marker"></div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <span class="timeline-date">2027</span>
            <h3>Governance Console launch</h3>
            <p>Enterprise governance product for fleet-scale policy enforcement and audit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ Investor CTA ═══ -->
  <section class="section section-alt" style="text-align: center;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">For investors and partners</h2>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin: 0 auto var(--space-xl);">
        AEROS is defining the governed runtime layer for embodied AI — a systems category that doesn't exist yet.
        We're looking for partners who understand infrastructure plays and are willing to invest in the platform layer.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-md); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Schedule a Call</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Request Materials</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  .page-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  .page-desc {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .page-desc em { font-style: normal; color: var(--primary); font-weight: 600; }
  .section-alt {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  /* ═══ Mission ═══ */
  .mission-block {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .mission-quote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .mission-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-body) !important;
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    font-weight: 400 !important;
    color: var(--text-secondary) !important;
    line-height: 1.7 !important;
  }

  /* ═══ Who We Are ═══ */
  .who-block {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .who-block p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  .who-block p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ═══ Why Us ═══ */
  .why-us-block {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .why-us-intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* ═══ Thesis / Cards ═══ */
  .thesis-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .thesis-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .thesis-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  .thesis-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .thesis-card p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ═══ Timeline ═══ */
  .timeline {
    max-width: 640px;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 7px;
    top: 8px;
    bottom: 8px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }
  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .timeline-item:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }

  .timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(-1 * var(--space-xl) + 2px);
    top: 6px;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--bg-base);
    border: 2px solid var(--border);
  }
  .done .timeline-marker {
    background: var(--success);
    border-color: var(--success);
  }

  .timeline-date {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .timeline-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0;
  }
  .timeline-content p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .timeline-item:not(.done) h3 { color: var(--text-muted); }
  .timeline-item:not(.done) p { color: var(--text-muted); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .thesis-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
